member.name: T:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.AzureMLUpdateResourceActivity
member.summary:
ADF Activity for updating the Trained Model module of an Azure ML Web service endpoint with a new trained model. See https://azure.microsoft.com/documentation/articles/machine-learning-retrain-models-programmatically/ for information on how to create retrainable Azure Machine Learning services. You can create an ADF Pipeline with an to perform retraining and produce a new iLearner in an output Dataset, then use that Dataset as input to this Activity to patch a batch scoring endpoint.
The Azure ML Linked Service for this activity must contain the management URL and API key.

member.name: P:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.AzureMLUpdateResourceActivity.TrainedModelName
member.summary: Required. Name of the Trained Model module in the experiment graph to be updated.

member.summary: Optional. The consistency level specifies how many Cassandra servers must respond to a read request before returning data to the client application. member.name: T:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel
member.summary: Consistency level when connecting to the Cassandra database. A property of . Reference: http://docs.datastax.com/en/cassandra/2.0/cassandra/dml/dml_config_consistency_c.html.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.All
member.summary: Returns the record after all replicas have responded. The read operation will fail if a replica does not respond.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.EachQuorum
member.summary: Returns the record once a quorum of replicas in each data center of the cluster has responded.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.Quorum
member.summary: Returns the record after a quorum of replicas has responded from any data center.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.LocalQuorum
member.summary: Returns the record after a quorum of replicas in the current data center as the coordinator has reported. Avoids latency of inter-data center communication.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.One
member.summary: Returns a response from the closest replica, as determined by the snitch. By default, a read repair runs in the background to make the other replicas consistent.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.Two
member.summary: Returns the most recent data from two of the closest replicas.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.Three
member.summary: Returns the most recent data from three of the closest replicas.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.LocalOne
member.summary: Returns a response from the closest replica in the local data center.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.Serial
member.summary: Allows reading the current (and possibly uncommitted) state of data without proposing a new addition or update. If a SERIAL read finds an uncommitted transaction in progress, it will commit the transaction as part of the read. Similar to QUORUM.

member.name: F:Microsoft.Azure.Management.DataFactories.Models.CassandraSourceReadConsistencyLevel.LocalSerial
member.summary: Same as SERIAL, but confined to the data center. Similar to LOCAL_QUORUM.
